    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The URL Loading System supports password-based user credentials, certificate-based user credentials, and certificate-based server credentials."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you create a credential, you can specify it for a single request, persist it temporarily (until your app quits), or persist it permanently. Permanent persistence can be local persistence in the keychain, or synchronized persistence across the user's devices, based on their Apple ID."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Permanent storage of credentials is only available for password-based credentials. TLS credentials are never stored permanently by "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/urlcredentialstorage"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". In general, use for-session persistence for TLS credentials."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
